NUMBER 2599
NAME Hill of Heroes
OUTDOOR_OTHER
FIXED_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
Golden braziers cast an eternal light over the top of the hill, illuminating
the marble benches and the one statue that are here. The benches are
arranged so as to allow unobstructed views of the surroundings. A gleaming
albescent statue of an armored woman brandishing a sword rests atop a
bronze pedestal beyond the benches.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT N 28
EXIT W 517
ITEM 0 346 ADJ1=423 ADJ2=1130
EXTEND 0 of an armored woman brandishing a sword
ITEM 1 292 ADJ1=265 ADJ2=39
EXTEND 1 that catches the sunlight and bathes the statue in a golden glow
ITEM 2 400 ADJ1=334
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 2
"Solaria Kentaurus, Princess of Fayd, 992 - 1018"
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
It is a statue of Princess Solaria, depicting her at her best:  leading
a battle charge, cresting a hill and hurling a challenge to the foe.
Her armor and sword gleam in the sunlight, while her features show the
strength and determination that characterized her life.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 1
The reflective surface of the pedestal reflects the available light onto
the statue bathing it in a beautiful golden glow. A small truesteel
plaque is set into the base of the pedestal.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFVERB RECALL -1
  ECHO PLAYER The golden glow is far stronger than can be explained by reflection, and you realize that the statue basks in Rorin's approval.
  ECHO OTHERS %N gazes, transfixed, at the statue.
ENDIF
